detaileddescription.para: Field id: 500 Location of the manifest file
Field id: 501 Length of the manifest file in bytes
Field id: 502 ID of a partition spec used to write the manifest; must be listed in table metadata partition-specs
Field id: 517 The type of files tracked by the manifest, either data or delete files; 0 for all v1 manifests
Field id: 515 The sequence number when the manifest was added to the table; use 0 when reading v1 manifest lists
Field id: 516 The minimum data sequence number of all live data or delete files in the manifest; use 0 when reading v1 manifest lists
Field id: 503 ID of the snapshot where the manifest file was added
Field id: 504 Number of entries in the manifest that have status ADDED (1), when null this is assumed to be non-zero
Field id: 505 Number of entries in the manifest that have status EXISTING (0), when null this is assumed to be non-zero
Field id: 506 Number of entries in the manifest that have status DELETED (2), when null this is assumed to be non-zero
Field id: 512 Number of rows in all of files in the manifest that have status ADDED, when null this is assumed to be non-zero
Field id: 513 Number of rows in all of files in the manifest that have status EXISTING, when null this is assumed to be non-zero
Field id: 514 Number of rows in all of files in the manifest that have status DELETED, when null this is assumed to be non-zero
Field id: 507 Element field id: 508 A list of field summaries for each partition field in the spec. Each field in the list corresponds to a field in the manifest file's partition spec.
Field id: 519 Implementation-specific key metadata for encryption
Field id: 520 The starting _row_id to assign to rows added by ADDED data files

memberdef.name: kManifestPath
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeRequired( kManifestPathFieldId, "manifest_path", string(), "Location URI with FS scheme")

memberdef.name: kManifestLength
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeRequired( kManifestLengthFieldId, "manifest_length", int64(), "Total file size in bytes")

memberdef.name: kPartitionSpecId
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeRequired( kPartitionSpecIdFieldId, "partition_spec_id", int32(), "Spec ID used to write")

memberdef.name: kContent
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeOptional( kContentFieldId, "content", int32(), "Contents of the manifest: 0=data, 1=deletes")

memberdef.name: kSequenceNumber
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeOptional(kSequenceNumberFieldId, "sequence_number", int64(), "Sequence number when the manifest was added")

memberdef.name: kMinSequenceNumber
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeOptional(kMinSequenceNumberFieldId, "min_sequence_number", int64(), "Lowest sequence number in the manifest")

memberdef.name: kAddedSnapshotId
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeRequired(kAddedSnapshotIdFieldId, "added_snapshot_id", int64(), "Snapshot ID that added the manifest")

memberdef.name: kPartitions
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeOptional( kPartitionSummaryFieldId, "partitions", list(SchemaField::MakeRequired(508, std::string(ListType::kElementName), struct_({ PartitionFieldSummary::kContainsNull, PartitionFieldSummary::kContainsNaN, PartitionFieldSummary::kLowerBound, PartitionFieldSummary::kUpperBound, }))), "Summary for each partition")

memberdef.name: kKeyMetadata
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeOptional( kKeyMetadataFieldId, "key_metadata", binary(), "Encryption key metadata blob")

memberdef.name: kFirstRowId
memberdef.initializer: = SchemaField::MakeOptional( kFirstRowIdFieldId, "first_row_id", int64(), "Starting row ID to assign to new rows in ADDED data files")

briefdescription.para: Checks if this manifest file contains entries with ADDED status.
Checks if this manifest file contains entries with EXISTING status.
Checks if this manifest file contains entries with DELETED status.
